<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>Hello, my NTFS volume that I shared with a Windows installation suddenly won&#39;t mount on Arch, the kernel goes into emergency mode because it can&#39;t mount the volume. So I then proceed to comment out my fstab entry :</p> <p><code># /dev/nvme0n1p3 (Disque E:) UUID=1065A6760ECF4599</code> </p> <p><code># /run/media/heimana/NVME ntfs3 uid=1000,gid=1000,rw,user,exec,umask=000,ssd 0 0</code></p> <p>When trying <code>mount -t ntfs3 /dev/nvme0n1p3</code>, it fail to mount saying :</p> <p><code>mount: /run/media/heimana/NVME: mauvais type de système de fichiers, option erronée, superbloc erroné sur /dev/nvme0n1p3, page de code ou programme auxiliaire manquant, ou autre erreur.</code><br/> <code>dmesg(1) peut avoir plus d&#39;informations après un échec de l&#39;appel système du montage.</code></p> <p>A.K.A : wrong fs type, erroned options, erroned superbloc on <code>/dev/nvme0n1p3</code>, page code or auxiliary program missing, or other errors ...</p> <p>same error when trying to mount the volume to <code>/mnt</code></p> <p>I´m running <code>5.18.11-arch1-1</code></p> <p>(Excuse my french btw)</p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/Yelloris"> /u/Yelloris </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w06zgr/fail_to_mount_ntfs_volume/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/w06zgr/fail_to_mount_ntfs_volume/">[comments]</a></span>